 - provides accessibility for fields,methods or constructors

 4 Types of access modifiers/access specifiers

 1. private
    - within a class only
    - not accessible out the class,package
    - class never be private


 2. default
    - can have access outside the class with same package
    - not accessible outside the package
    - can have access in sub class
    - no need to specify default keyword

 3. protected
    - access within a package
    - not accessible outside the package
    - through the child or by extending the class we can access protected data member
        outside the package(through the inheritance only)

 4. public
    - access everywhere

Homework:
1. why we cannot declare class as private?